  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening of science-policy-society interfaces</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed activity covers four lines of action all aimed at strengthening the science-policy-society interface: promotion of Science Diplomacy; science advice for sustainability science; popularization of Science; UNESCO support to Science-Policy Platform on Biodiversity and Ecosystem Services (IPBES) and the global change research for integrated policy (Future earth). These are essential tools to achieve peace and sustainable development worldwide, especially for their role in solving trans-boundary issues. They aim at fostering awareness in STI and at developing collaborative approaches among scientists, policy makers, entrepreneurs, youth, women, NGOs and society. To implement this activity a network of partners is involved including, among others The World Academy of Science (TWAS).</narrative>
  </description>
